1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Nearby stars shift as Earth moves—this shift reveals their distance.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,400
This phenomenon is called stellar parallax.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,000
It's all about perspective.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,200
As Earth orbits the Sun, stars appear to slightly shift against the background.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:17,200
Using trigonometry, astronomers calculate distances based on this tiny shift.

6
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,600
This method allows us to measure stars thousands of light-years away!

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,600
Curious about more cosmic mysteries?

8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,000
Like and subscribe for more insights!
